---
layout: layout.njk
title: Privacy Notice
description: How TechZeph handles personal data, cookies, and analytics for UK visitors.
permalink: /privacy/
---
<article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-950 sm:text-4xl">Privacy Notice</h1>
  <p class="mt-4 text-slate-700">
    This notice explains how TechZeph handles personal data and cookie preferences when you use this website.
    It is written for UK visitors and aligned to UK GDPR and PECR principles.
  </p>
  <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-600">Last updated: {{ privacy.lastUpdated | dateDmy }}</p>

  <div class="panel mt-8 p-6 sm:p-8">
    <div class="space-y-6 text-slate-800 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_h3]:text-lg [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_li]:leading-7 [&_p]:leading-7 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:space-y-1 [&_ul]:pl-6">
      <section>
        <h2>1) Who Controls Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          Data controller: <strong>{{ privacy.controllerName }}</strong><br>
          Contact: <a class="text-blue-700 hover:underline" href="mailto:{{ privacy.contactEmail }}">{{ privacy.contactEmail }}</a><br>
          Data protection contact: {{ privacy.dataProtectionContact }}<br>
          Postal address: {{ privacy.postalAddress }}
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>2) Data We Process</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Basic technical data needed to run the website (for example, request metadata and security logs).</li>
          <li>Cookie preference data so we can remember your consent choices.</li>
          <li>Aggregated traffic analytics data from Cloudflare Web Analytics.</li>
          <li>Information you send us directly (for example by email).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>3) Why We Process Data (Lawful Basis)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> site security, fraud prevention, and service improvement.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> where retention is required by law.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>4) Cookies And Similar Technologies</h2>
        <p>
          We currently use strictly necessary cookies for core site functionality and preference controls.
          We do not currently set optional analytics cookies from this website.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can read full details on our <a class="text-blue-700 hover:underline" href="{{ '/cookies/' | url }}">Cookie Policy</a>.
          You can also update your choice at any time using the button below.
        </p>
        <button data-open-cookie-preferences="true" type="button" class="inline-flex items-center rounded-lg bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-blue-700">
          Cookie settings
        </button>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>5) Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          We use Cloudflare Web Analytics to understand high-level site usage and performance trends.
        </p>
        <p>
          This helps us improve content quality and usability. We do not currently run a custom event analytics
          stack for affiliate click tracking.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>6) Affiliate Links</h2>
        <p>
          Some pages include affiliate links. Clicking one may send you to a third-party website with its own
          privacy and cookie policies. This does not change the price you pay.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>7) Data Sharing And Processors</h2>
        <p>
          We may use third-party service providers for hosting, analytics, and operations. These providers process
          data on our instructions where required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>8) Retention</h2>
        <p>
          We retain personal data only for as long as needed for the purpose it was collected, including legal,
          accounting, and security obligations.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>9) Your Rights</h2>
        <p>Under UK GDPR, you may have rights to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Access a copy of your personal data.</li>
          <li>Request correction of inaccurate data.</li>
          <li>Request deletion in certain circumstances.</li>
          <li>Object to or restrict some processing.</li>
          <li>Withdraw consent at any time for consent-based processing.</li>
          <li>Lodge a complaint with the UK ICO.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>10) Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy questions, contact
          <a class="text-blue-700 hover:underline" href="mailto:{{ privacy.contactEmail }}">{{ privacy.contactEmail }}</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>
